10 "§ 88B-4. Powers and duties of the Board.
11 (a) The Board shall have the following powers and duties:
12 (1) To administer and interpret this Chapter.
13 (2) To adopt, amend, and repeal rules to carry out the provisions of this Chapter.
14 (3) To examine and determine the qualifications and fitness of applicants for
15 licensure under this Chapter.
16 (4) To issue, renew, deny, restrict, suspend, or revoke licenses.
17 (5) To conduct investigations of alleged violations of this Chapter or the Board's
18 rules.
19 (6) To collect fees required by G.S. 88B-20 and any other monies permitted by
20 law to be paid to the Board.
21 (7) To approve new cosmetic art schools.
22 (7a) To adopt rules for cosmetic art schools.
23 (8) To inspect cosmetic art schools and shops.schools, cosmetic art shops, and
24 mobile cosmetic art shops.
25 (9) To adopt rules for the sanitary management and physical requirements of
26 cosmetic art shops shops, mobile cosmetic art shops, and cosmetic art schools.
27 (10) To establish a curriculum for each course of study required for the issuance of
28 a license or certification issued under this Chapter.
29 (11) To employ an executive director and any additional professional, clerical, or
30 special personnel necessary to carry out the provisions of this Chapter, and to
31 purchase or rent necessary office space, equipment, and supplies.
32 (12) To adopt a seal.
33 (13) To carry out any other actions authorized by this Chapter.
34 (b) A member of the Board shall have the authority to inspect cosmetic art shops shops,
35 mobile cosmetic art shops, and cosmetic art schools at any reasonable hour to determine
36 compliance with the provisions of this Chapter if the inspection is made: (i) at the request of the
37 Board, or with the approval of the chair or the executive director as the result of a complaint
38 made to the Board or a problem reported by an inspector, or (ii) at the request of an inspector
39 who deems it necessary to request the assistance of a Board member and who has the prior
40 approval of the chair or executive director to do so. A Board member who makes an inspection
41 pursuant to this subsection shall file a report with the Board before requesting reimbursement for
42 expenses.
43 (c) The Board shall keep a record of its proceedings relating to the issuance, renewal,
44 denial, restriction, suspension, and revocation of licenses. licenses and certifications. This record
45 shall also contain each licensee's name, business and home addresses, license number, and the
46 date the license was issued.
47 (d) The Board shall offer or approve a 10-hour course in infection control for natural hair
48 care specialists. The Board shall make available at least one qualifying course on its website, free
49 of charge.
50 "§ 88B-5. Meetings and compensation of the Board.
Senate Bill 808-Third Edition Page 3

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (a) Each member of the Board shall receive compensation for services and expenses as
2 provided in G.S. 93B-5, but shall be limited to payment for services deemed official business of
3 the Board when such business exceeds three continuous hours per day. Official business of the
4 Board includes meetings called by the chair and time spent inspecting cosmetic art shops and
5 shops, mobile cosmetic art shops, and cosmetic art schools as permitted by this Chapter. No
6 payment for per diem or travel expenses shall be authorized or paid for Board meetings other
7 than those called by the chair. The Board may annually select one member to attend a national
8 state board of cosmetic arts meeting on official business of the Board. No other Board members
9 shall be authorized to attend trade shows or to travel out-of-state at the Board's expense.
10 (b) The Board shall hold four regular meetings a year in the months of January, April,
11 July, and October. The chair may call additional meetings whenever necessary.
12 "§ 88B-6. Board office, employees, funds, budget requirements.
13 (a) The Board shall maintain its office in Wake County, North Carolina.
14 (b) The Board shall employ an executive director who shall not be a member of the Board.
15 The executive director shall keep all records of the Board, issue all necessary notices, and
16 perform any other duties required by the Board.
17 (c) With the approval of the Director of the Budget and the Office of State Human
18 Resources, the Board may employ as many inspectors, investigators, and other staff as necessary
19 to perform inspections and other duties prescribed by the Board. Inspectors and investigators
20 shall be experienced in all parts of cosmetic art and shall have authority to examine cosmetic art
21 shops shops, mobile cosmetic art shops, and cosmetic art schools during business hours to
22 determine compliance with this Chapter.
23 "§ 88B-7. Qualifications for licensing cosmetologists.
24 The Board shall issue a license to practice as a cosmetologist to any individual who meets all
25 of the following requirements:
26 (1) Successful completion of at least 1,500 1,200 hours of a cosmetology
27 curriculum in an approved cosmetic art school, or at least 1,200 hours of a
28 cosmetology curriculum in an approved cosmetic art school and completion
29 of an apprenticeship for a period of at least six months under the direct
30 supervision of a cosmetologist, as certified by sworn affidavit of three licensed
31 cosmetologists or by other evidence satisfactory to the Board.school.
32 (2) Passage of an examination conducted by the Board.
33 (3) Payment of the fees required by G.S. 88B-20.
34 "§ 88B-8. Qualifications for licensing apprentices.
35 The Board shall issue a license to practice as an apprentice to any individual who meets all
36 of the following requirements:
37 (1) Successful completion of at least 1,200 hours of a cosmetology curriculum in
38 an approved cosmetic art school.
39 (2) Passage of an examination conducted by the Board.
40 (3) Payment of the fees required by G.S. 88B-20.
41 "§ 88B-8.1. Qualifications for licensing as a hair designer.
42 The Board shall issue a license to practice as a hair designer to any individual who meets all
43 of the following requirements:
44 (1) Successful completion of at least 900 hours of a hair design curriculum in an
45 approved cosmetic art school.
46 (2) Passage of an examination conducted by the Board.
47 (3) Payment of the fees required by G.S. 88B-20.
48 "§ 88B-9. Qualifications for licensing as an esthetician.
49 The Board shall issue a license to practice as an esthetician to any individual who meets all
50 of the following requirements:
