31 "§ 88B-12. Temporary employment permit; extensions; limits on practice.
32 (a) The Board shall issue a temporary employment permit to an applicant for licensure
33 as an apprentice, a cosmetologist, hair designer, esthetician, natural hair care specialist, or
34 manicurist who meets all of the following:
35 (1) Has completed the required hours of a cosmetic art school curriculum in the
36 area in which the applicant wishes to be licensed.
37 (2) Has applied to take the examination within three months of completing the
38 required hours.
39 (3) Is qualified to take the examination.
40 (b) A temporary employment permit shall expire six months from the date of graduation
41 from a cosmetic art school and shall not be renewed.
42 (c) The holder of a temporary employment permit may practice cosmetic art only under
43 the supervision of a licensed cosmetologist, hair designer, manicurist, natural hair care specialist,
44 or esthetician, as appropriate, and may not operate a cosmetic art shop.
45 "§ 88B-13. Applicants licensed in other states.
46 (a) The Board shall issue a license to an applicant licensed as an apprentice, a
47 cosmetologist, hair designer, esthetician, natural hair care specialist, or manicurist in another
48 state if the applicant shows:
49 (1) The applicant is an active practitioner in good standing.
50 (2) The applicant has practiced at least one of the three years immediately
51 preceding the application for a license.
