12 requirements in the state in which the teacher is licensed shall be substantially equivalent to those
13 required in this State and that the applicant shall be licensed by the Board to practice in the area
14 in which the applicant is licensed to teach.
15 "§ 88B-14. Licensing of cosmetic art shops.shops and mobile cosmetic art shops.
16 (a) The Board shall issue a license to operate a cosmetic art shop or mobile cosmetic art
17 shop to any applicant who submits a properly completed application, on a form approved by the
18 Board, pays the required fee, and is determined, after inspection, to be in compliance with the
19 provisions of this Chapter and the Board's rules.
20 (b) The applicant shall list all licensees who practice cosmetic art in the shop or mobile
21 cosmetic art shop and shall identify each as an employee or a booth renter.
22 (c) A cosmetic art shop or mobile cosmetic art shop shall be allowed to operate for a
23 period of 30 days while the Board inspects and determines the shop's or mobile cosmetic art
24 shop's compliance with this Chapter and the Board's rules. If the Board is unable to complete the
25 inspection within 30 days, the shop or mobile cosmetic art shop will be authorized to operate
26 until such an inspection can be completed.
27 (d) A license to operate a cosmetic art shop or mobile cosmetic art shop shall not be
28 transferable from one location to another or from one owner to another.
29 "§ 88B-15. Practice outside cosmetic art shops.
30 (a) Any individual licensed or certified under this Chapter may visit the residences of
31 individuals who are sick or disabled and confined to their places of residence in order to attend
32 to their cosmetic needs. A licensed or certified individual may also visit hospitals, nursing homes,
33 rest homes, retirement homes, mental institutions, correctional facilities, funeral homes, and
34 similar institutions to attend to the cosmetic needs of those in these institutions.
35 (b) An individual licensed or certified under this Chapter may practice in a licensed
36 barbershop as permitted by G.S. 86A-14.G.S. 86B-32.
37 (c) A natural hair care specialist certified under this Chapter may practice natural hair
38 care at fairs, street festivals, holiday festivals, agricultural festivals, farmers markets, balloon
39 races, local fundraisers, and other similar events approved by the Board.
40 "§ 88B-15A. Mobile cosmetic art shops.
41 (a) The Board shall issue a license to operate a mobile cosmetic art shop to any applicant
42 who submits a properly completed application on a form approved by the Board, pays the
43 required fee, and is determined after inspection to be in compliance with the provisions of this
44 Chapter and the Board's rules.
45 (b) The Board shall adopt rules for the operation, permitting, and inspection of mobile
46 cosmetic art shops, including standards for facilities, personnel, and safety and sanitary
47 requirements. All permitting and operating requirements provided by this Chapter or by rules
48 adopted by the Board pursuant to this Chapter that apply to cosmetic art shops shall also apply
49 to mobile cosmetic art shops, except to the extent that the requirements conflict with this section
50 or with any rules adopted by the Board pursuant to this section.
