1 (c) In addition to the requirements of this Chapter, individuals and the vehicles they
2 operate while providing mobile cosmetic art services shall be subject to the provisions of (i)
3 Chapter 20 of the General Statutes, (ii) Title 19A of the North Carolina Administrative Code,
4 (iii) all applicable OSHA requirements, and (iv) all local laws and ordinances regulating business
5 establishments.
6 (d) A mobile cosmetic art shop must be equipped with a functional sink and toilet
7 facilities and must maintain an adequate supply of clean water and wastewater storage capacity.
8 (e) No cosmetic art service may be performed in a mobile cosmetic art shop while the
9 mobile cosmetic art shop is moving. The mobile cosmetic art shop must be safely parked in a
10 legal parking spot at all times while patrons are present inside the mobile cosmetic art shop.
11 (f) A mobile cosmetic art shop owner must maintain a permanent business address at
12 which records of appointments, itineraries, license numbers, and vehicle identification numbers
13 for each mobile cosmetic art shop being operated shall be kept and made available for verification
14 and inspection by the Board and at which all correspondence from the Board can be received.
15 (g) To facilitate periodic inspections of mobile cosmetic art shops, prior to the beginning
16 of each month, the owner of the mobile cosmetic art shop shall provide to the Board a written
17 monthly itinerary listing locations, dates, and hours of operation for the mobile cosmetic art shop.
