13 "§ 88B-21. Renewals; expired licenses; inactive status.
14 (a) Each license to operate a cosmetic art shop or mobile cosmetic art shop shall be
15 renewed on or before the first day of February of each year. As provided in G.S. 88B-20, a late
16 fee shall be charged for licenses renewed after February 1. Any license not renewed by March 1
17 of each year shall expire. A cosmetic art shop or mobile cosmetic art shop whose license has
18 been expired for one year or less shall have the license reinstated immediately upon payment of
19 the reinstatement fee, the late fee, and all unpaid license fees. The licensee shall submit to the
20 Board, as a part of the renewal process, a list of all licensed cosmetologists who practice cosmetic
21 art in the shop and shall identify each as an employee or a booth renter.
22 (b) Cosmetologist licenses shall be renewed on or before October 1 every three years
23 beginning October 1, 1998. A late fee shall be charged for renewals after that date. Any license
24 not renewed shall expire on October 1 of the year that renewal is required. The Board may
25 develop and implement a plan for staggered license renewal and may prorate license fees to
26 implement such a plan.
27 (c) Apprentice, Hair designer, esthetician, natural hair care specialist, and manicurist
28 licenses or certifications shall be renewed annually on or before October 1 of each year. A late
29 fee shall be charged for the renewal of licenses or certifications after that date. Any license or
30 certification not renewed shall expire on October 1 of that year.
31 (d) Teacher licenses shall be renewed every two years on or before October 1. A late fee
32 shall be charged for the renewal of licenses after that date. Any license not renewed shall expire
33 on October 1 of that year.
34 (e) Prior to renewal of a certification or license, a teacher, cosmetologist, hair designer,
35 esthetician, natural hair care specialist, or manicurist shall annually complete eight four hours of
36 Board-approved continuing education for each year of the licensing cycle. A cosmetologist may
37 complete up to 24 hours 12 hours of required continuing education at any time within the
38 cosmetologist's three-year licensing cycle. Licensees shall submit written documentation to the
39 Board showing that they have satisfied the requirements of this subsection. A licensee who is in
40 active practice as a cosmetologist, hair designer, esthetician, natural hair care specialist, or
41 manicurist, has practiced for at least 10 consecutive years in that profession, and is 60 years of
42 age or older does not have to meet the continuing education requirements of this subsection. A
43 licensee who is in active practice as a cosmetologist cosmetologist, hair designer, esthetician,
44 natural hair care specialist, or manicurist and has at least 20 consecutive years of experience as a
45 cosmetologist, in that profession, does not have to meet the continuing education requirements
46 of this subsection, but shall report any continuing education classes completed to the Board,
47 whether the continuing education classes are Board-approved or not. Promotion of products and
48 systems shall be allowed at continuing education given in-house or at trade shows. Continuing
49 education classes may also be offered in secondary languages as needed. No member of the Board
50 may offer continuing education courses as required by this section.
Senate Bill 808-Third Edition Page 9

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (f) If an apprentice, a cosmetologist, hair designer, esthetician, manicurist, natural hair
2 care specialist, or teacher fails to renew his or her license or certification within five years
3 following the expiration date, the licensee shall be required to pass an examination as prescribed
4 by the Board before the license will be reinstated.
5 (g) Cosmetic art school licenses shall be renewed on or before October 1 of each year. A
6 late fee shall be charged for licenses renewed after that date. Any license not renewed by
7 November 1 of that year shall expire. A cosmetic art school whose license has been expired for
8 one year or less shall have its license reinstated upon payment of the reinstatement fee, the late
9 fee, and all unpaid license fees.
10 (h) Upon request by a licensee for inactive status, the Board may place the licensee's
11 name on the inactive list so long as the licensee is in good standing with the Board. An inactive
12 licensee is not required to complete continuing education requirements. An inactive licensee shall
13 not practice cosmetic art for consideration. However, the inactive licensee may continue to
14 purchase supplies as accorded an active licensee. When the inactive licensee desires to be
15 removed from the inactive list and return to active practice, the inactive licensee shall notify the
16 Board of his or her desire to return to active status and pay the required fee as determined by the
17 Board. As a condition of returning to active status, the Board may require the licensee to complete
18 eight to 24 hours of continuing education pursuant to subsection (e) of this section.
19 "§ 88B-22. Licenses and certifications required; criminal penalty.
20 (a) Except as provided in this Chapter, no person may practice or attempt to practice
21 cosmetic art for pay or reward in any form, either directly or indirectly, without being licensed
22 or certified as an apprentice, a cosmetologist, hair designer, esthetician, natural hair care
23 specialist, or manicurist by the Board.
24 (b) Except as provided in this Chapter, no person may practice cosmetic art or any part
25 of cosmetic art, for pay or reward in any form, either directly or indirectly, outside of a licensed
26 cosmetic art shop.shop or mobile cosmetic art shop.
27 (c) No person may open or operate a cosmetic art shop or mobile cosmetic art shop in
28 this State unless a license has been issued by the Board for that shop.shop or mobile cosmetic art
29 shop.
30 (d) An individual certified or licensed as an esthetician, hair designer, natural hair care
31 specialist, or manicurist may practice only that part of cosmetic art for which the individual is
32 certified or licensed.
33 (d1) No person may teach cosmetic art in a Board-approved cosmetic art school unless the
34 person is a teacher licensed under this Chapter. A guest lecturer may be exempt from the
35 requirements of this subsection upon approval by the Board.
36 (e) An apprentice licensed under the provisions of this Chapter shall apprentice under the
37 direct supervision of a cosmetologist. An apprentice shall not operate a cosmetic art shop.
38 (f) A violation of this Chapter is a Class 3 misdemeanor.
39 "§ 88B-23. Licenses and certifications to be posted.
40 (a) Every apprentice, cosmetologist, hair designer, esthetician, manicurist, natural hair
41 care specialist, and teacher licensed under this Chapter shall display the certificate of license
42 issued by the Board within the shop in which the person works.
43 (b) Every certificate of license to operate a cosmetic art shop or shop, mobile cosmetic
44 art shop, or cosmetic art school shall be conspicuously posted in the shop or school for which it
45 is issued.
46 (c) Every natural hair care specialist shall conspicuously display the infection control
47 certification issued by the Board at any place where the natural hair care specialist is practicing
48 natural hair care.
49 "§ 88B-24. Revocation of licenses and other disciplinary measures.
50 The Board may restrict, suspend, revoke, or refuse to issue, renew, or reinstate any license
51 for any of the following:
Page 10 Senate Bill 808-Third Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (1) Conviction of a felony shown by certified copy of the record of the court of
2 conviction.
3 (2) Gross malpractice or gross incompetency as determined by the Board.
4 (3) Advertising by means of knowingly false or deceptive statements.
5 (4) Permitting any individual to practice cosmetic art without a license license,
6 infection control certification, or temporary employment permit, with an
7 expired license or temporary employment permit, or with an invalid license
8 license, infection control certification, or temporary employment permit.
9 (5) Obtaining or attempting to obtain a license for money or other thing of value
10 other than the required fee or by fraudulent misrepresentation.
11 (6) Practicing or attempting to practice by fraudulent misrepresentation.
12 (7) Willful failure to display a certificate of license or an infection control
13 certification as required by G.S. 88B-23.
14 (8) Willful violation of the rules adopted by the Board.
15 (9) Violation of G.S. 86A-15 G.S. 86B-31 by a cosmetologist, hair designer,
16 esthetician, natural hair care specialist, or manicurist licensed or certified by
17 the Board and practicing cosmetic art in a barber shop.
18 "§ 88B-25. Exemptions.
19 The following persons are exempt from the provisions of this Chapter while engaged in the
20 proper discharge of their professional duties:
21 (1) Undertakers and funeral establishments licensed under G.S. 90-210.25.
22 (2) Persons authorized to practice medicine or surgery under Chapter 90 of the
23 General Statutes.
24 (3) Nurses licensed under Chapter 90 of the General Statutes.
25 (4) Commissioned medical or surgical officers of the United States Army, Air
26 Force, Navy, Marine Corps, Space Force, or Coast Guard.
27 (5) A person employed in a cosmetic art shop or mobile cosmetic art shop whose
28 duties are expressly confined to the shampooing or blow drying of hair,
29 provided that the person shall comply with rules adopted by the Board relating
30 to sanitary management of cosmetic art shops.shops and mobile cosmetic art
31 shops.
32 "§ 88B-26. Rules to be posted.
33 (a) The Board shall furnish a copy of its rules relating to sanitary management of
34 cosmetic art shops shops, mobile cosmetic art shops, and cosmetic art schools to each shop shop,
35 mobile cosmetic art shop, and school licensed by the Board. Each shop shop, mobile cosmetic
36 art shop, and school shall post the rules in a conspicuous place.
37 (b) The Board shall furnish a copy of its rules relating to curriculum and schools to each
38 licensed cosmetic art school. Each cosmetic art school shall make these rules available to all
39 teachers and students.
40 "§ 88B-27. Inspections.
41 Any inspector or other authorized representative of the Board may enter any cosmetic art
42 shop or shop, mobile cosmetic art shop, or cosmetic art school to inspect it for compliance with
43 this Chapter and the Board's rules. All persons practicing cosmetic art in a shop shop, mobile
44 cosmetic art shop, or school shall, upon request, present satisfactory proof of identification.
45 Satisfactory proof shall be in the form of a photographic driver's license or photographic
46 identification card issued by any state, federal, or other government entity. The Board may
47 require a cosmetic art shop or shop, mobile cosmetic art shop, or cosmetic art school to be
48 inspected as a condition for license renewal.
49 …."
